data.title: Medical Tubing in or near Texas
data.meta_description: Medical Tubing Suppliers located in Texas - North
data.text:
Distributor of polyurethane and nylon tubing. Available in 1/4 to 21/64 in. ID and 3/8 to 1/2 in. OD sizes.

Distributor of polyurethane, polyethylene, PTFE and PVC dispensing tubes. Specifications include 0.152 to 0.75 in. O.D. and 0.093 to 0.25 in. I.D. Used for pinch tube valves and dispensers. Serves defense, battery, lighting, medical, power and transportation industries.

Custom manufacturer of Ultra PrecisionÂ® and direct extruded tubes for the automotive and medical industries. Made from 1000, 2000, 3000, 5000, 6000, 6061, and 6063 aluminum alloys. Available in round, rectangular, and square shapes. Additional services such as bending, anodizing, and computer numerical control (CNC) machining are also provided. Prototype and high volume production runs available.

Distributor of unreinforced polyvinyl chloride (PVC) tubing for medical, surgical and hospital applications. Available in various length and in 1/16 to 3 in. dia. 24/7 services and stock items available. Same day shipping.

Supplier of tubing made from aluminum, steel and stainless steel materials. Available in round, rectangular and square forms with annealed, CDS, SCRE, DOM, HFS and hydraulic type configurations. Cut-off to specifications tubing is offered. Some tubing is resistant to corrosion and heat. Suitable for mechanical and structural purposes. Serves the automotive, electrical, aerospace, transportation, defense, technology and construction industries. Some tubing meets ASTM standards.

Custom manufacturer of plastic tubing for the medical industry. Made from high density polyethylene, ABS, polyethylene terephthalate glycol, polycarbonate and FR blended alloys. Available in 0.5 in. to ft. OD, 0.375 in. to 4.875 ft. ID, 1 in. to 16 ft. wall thickness. Tolerance ranges from 0.030 to 12 in. Comes in oval, round and square shapes. Tubes are corrosion, electrical, moisture, rust and UV resistant. Fabrication methods include extruding, forming and mandrel forming. Prototype and low to high volume production runs available. Meets ASTM and ANSI standards. FDA approved. ITAR registered. RoHS compliant. UL listed. NADCAP and CE certified.

Manufacturer of packaging materials and medical devices for the nutraceuticals, food and beverage, medical, pharmaceutical, personal care and household industries. Made from rubber, plastic, high-density polyethylene (HDPE), polypropylene (PP) polyethylene terephthalate (PET), polyvinyl chloride (PVC) and glass. Products include compounds, tuning, gaskets, stoppers, seals, hoses, containers, foils, liners and laminated films. Types of tubing are single and multi-lumen, coextruded, striped and braided. Suitable for intravenous therapy, respiratory, renal/dialysis, anesthesia, diagnostic and surgical equipment applications.

Custom manufacturer of catheter, nutrition feeding, peristaltic pump and gas transfer tubing made from silicone. Tubing is antimicrobial and X-ray or UV radiation, chemical and heat resistant. Serves the medical industry. RoHS compliant. FDA approved. Made in the USA.

Stocking distributor of insulation products for the aerospace and defense, medical, electrical, electronic and transportation industries. Product line includes adhesives, sealants, electrical protection sleeving, cable ties, fastening systems, hand tools, connectors, heat shrinkable tubing, convoluted tubing, terminals, splices, bus insulation products, tapes, fittings, heating tools and conveyor ovens. Value added services include tube and sleeve cutting, kitting to specifications and printing on tubing, markers, labels and cable ties.

Manufacturer of metal tubing for medical use. Materials include brass, carbon steel and stainless steel. Available in various sizes. Capabilities include tapering, cutting, reaming, chamfering, grooving, machining and bending. Vendor managed inventory (VMI) programs, stock items and 24/7 services available. Meets ASTM standards. On-time delivery. Made in USA.

ISO 9001:2008 & AS 9100:2004 certified worldwide distributor of standard & custom metal tubing including medical & surgical tubing. Available in titanium & chromium-cobalt molybdenum alloys. Titanium tubing ranges in ODs from 1/4 in. to 8 in. & wall thicknesses from 0.016 in. to 0.260 in. Value added services include abrasive sawing, waterjet/laser cutting, PVC coating, vibratory finishing, kitting, tube assembly, packaging & fabrication. JIT delivery available.

Contract manufacturer of tubing sets for pharmaceutical, medical, cosmetics, dietary supplements and veterinary industries. Capabilities include product design or development, contract and private label manufacturing. Secondary services such as sterilization, assembly, regulatory or laboratory testing, marketing and packaging are also offered. Suitable for wound care, ophthalmic, disposables and fixation applications. Small to large run production volume are available. FDA approved.

Manufacturer & custom manufacturer of tubings such as tubings for laboratory, medical & instrument use. Medical tubings include medical catheter, device, flexible metal, metal & stainless steel tubing. Choices available in shape & alloy, imperial & metric sizes, small/bulk orders. Consistency maintained in production. Industries served include OEMs such as aircraft, aerospace, chemical, gas, electronics, marine, medical, military, nuclear, oil, petrochemical, shipbuilding, & telecommunication. Compliant to standards including ASTM, ASME, BS, SAE & Military Specs.

ISO 9001:2015 certified. Distributor of plastic tubing for aerospace, defense, medical, pharmaceutical, transportation, oil, gas, food and beverage processing industries. Acrylic, vinyl, low density polyethylene (LDPE), polyurethane, PTFE and nylon tubing are offered. Available in various diameters, thicknesses lengths and widths. Features include clear, flexible, resistant to impact, atmospheric ozone, hydrolytic degradation and abrasion. Suitable for instrumentation, distilled, deionized, demineralized or reverse osmosis-treated water, handling petroleum-based products, high purity applications. FDA approved. Blanket orders accepted. ITAR registered. JIT delivery.

Manufacturer of standard and nitrogenized ACR copper tubing for medical oxygen gas applications. Available in K, L, M and DWV types with outside diameters ranging from 3/8 to 3-1/8 inches. Also offers copper tubes in hard or soft lengths and soft coils and standard and plastic-coated dehydrated refrigeration tubes and coils. Markets served include appliance, aerospace, automotive, military and recreational. Meets ASTM B-88, B-306 and B-280 standards. NSF approved. Made in USA.
